critical_positive: I think were able to move past the small talk quickly and gain a quick rapport. I felt that everyone was at ease and able to open up quickly and find commonalities between both parties. Both sides were able to take turns and take the lead. critical_negative: The only thing that really did not go well was at one point my partner wanted to talk about Covid news. For me this is not an enjoyable topic or a topic of interest.   I quickly was able to neutralize that topic and redirect it to a more desirable topic (from my perspective).

begin_memory_text: We greeted each other and began talking.  My chat partner was a retaker and had experience doing this so he explained that it will be a conversation with no set topic or questions.  I took it as a small talk with a perfect stranger.  We introduced each other, talked about Prolific experience, types of studies, covid situation in our respective areas, weather, AI and experience teaming up with robo chat partners
middle_memory_text: We talked about COVID situation in detail.  I shared that I am from one of the hardest hit state, so taking precautions, importance of flu shots which my chat partner already took.  I shared that after this, I plan to go out for a walk with my daughter, it is a nice day out with 75 degrees...beautiful fall day.  I also shared that we were hit with a storm a couple of days ago...many lost power and internet connections, trees came down.  The storm came out of nowhere, lasted only for 20 minutes and disappeared.  My chat partner shared his experiences with Prolific studies, he has been doing the studies for last 4 to 5 months and completed 267 studies to date, some he returned due to not worth the time or technical issues.  I mentioned that I found out about Prolific on a message board and wanted to explore as a side gig...as we are all living in a gig economy.  And its fun to share opinions and help universities with research.
end_memory_text: My chat partner talked about weird job interview questions and how he feels about it.  I also shared my experiences with them.  He said if they ask these type of questions, he isn't interested working there.  He also said it is 90 degrees in Houston and very hot...they are long way to fall weather.  All in all it was a pleasant conversation on varied topics...covid, weather, my current location, where I am originally from and how I feel about warm weather, Prolific studies, experience with IA/robo chat partners, and weird interview questions such as what's your favorite animal and my answer was peacock for elegance, colors and national bird of my home country.  We also talked about manholes and their shapes and counts.
rest_of_day_open: It will be busy since it is a Holiday weekend, have tasks lined up.  Nice weather so want to take advantage of.  Want to catch up on some Netflix and work with my daughter on a project I kept putting off.  Visit my next door neighbor to drop off a bag of apples I got from an apple picking farm trip yesterday
critical_positive: The conversation flow was smooth, no technical difficulties.  There were no awkward pauses even though there was no set topic of discussion.  A small talk conversation which went well on many topics...sharing Prolific study experiences, weather, covid, interview questions and experiences.  Uninterrupted conversation about situations around living life.  No big, deep or heated discussions.
critical_negative: There were no technical issues, nor any interruptions.  Conversation on simple every day life topics and how we deal with them.  No disagreements, or heated discussions.  It felt like a conversation you typically would have when your flight is delayed for hours and you are waiting and killing time until boarding time and strike up a conversation with fellow passengers while waiting.
